Automatic Crude Fat Analyzer is a specialized laboratory instrument designed to accurately and efficiently measure crude fat content in diverse samples. It typically employs extraction techniques such as Soxhlet or advanced solvent‑based methods, automating fat extraction, separation and quantification while eliminating manual, time‑consuming steps. Precise sensors and control systems ensure reproducible results, making the analyzer essential for food science, agriculture, feed analysis and biochemical research where reliable fat data support quality control, nutritional labeling and scientific investigations.

